Package: RateScape
Title: Branch-Specific Rate Variation for Complex Discrete Character Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Heath", "Blackmon", email = "coleoguy@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0590-2413"))
    )
Description: Infers branch-specific rate variation under arbitrary
    continuous-time Markov models for discrete character evolution on
    phylogenies. Implements a spike-and-slab Bayesian framework to identify
    branches evolving faster or slower than the background rate, a
    discretized-gamma maximum likelihood approach, and produces painted
    phylogenies depicting the spatial distribution of rate heterogeneity.
    Accepts any user-specified Q matrix, making it applicable to chromosome
    number evolution, morphological characters, biogeographic models, and
    other complex discrete traits. Core likelihood computations are
    implemented in C++ via Rcpp/RcppArmadillo for performance.
